== B.4 — Sourcing Notes

*Glassware and laboratory supplies:* Standard borosilicate laboratory glassware is available from scientific supply companies in most jurisdictions. In the United States, suppliers include Sigma-Aldrich/MilliporeSigma, Quark Glass, and various Amazon/eBay laboratory glassware vendors. Check that items are explicitly labelled borosilicate; soda-lime glass is not suitable for heating operations.

*Heating equipment:* A variable-temperature electric heating mantle provides the most control for Year One distillation and digestion work. A seed propagator or reptile warming mat can substitute for a low-temperature water bath if carefully monitored.

*Respirators:* P100 half-face respirators are available from hardware suppliers (3M, Moldex). Ensure cartridges are rated for particulates (P100) and not gases only. For antimony calcination, particulate-rated cartridges are essential.

*Antimony/stibnite:* Raw stibnite specimens are available from mineralogical suppliers, lapidary suppliers, and specimen dealers. Chinese stibnite (Hunan province) is the most commonly available and appropriate for laboratory work. Confirm purity with the supplier where possible; avoid specimens with artificial surface treatments.

*Metals for meditation (Year Two Month 11):* Lead fishing weights are available at any sporting goods store. Copper sheet, iron nails, tin solder, and small silver coins are available at hardware and jewellery supply stores. Gold: even 9-karat gold is adequate for meditative purposes.